In the dependency tree:
- Each tuple consists of the index of the word (token index), the word itself, and the index of its head (the word it depends on).
- The root of the tree (here, "förstår" with index 11) has a head index of 3, which is the verb "man" indicating the core action of the sentence. All other words relate to this structure accordingly.